## **Interactive Information Dashboard Design: reactable and reactablefmtr methods**

Create interactive information dashboard by using [reactable](https://glin.github.io/reactable/) and [reactablefmtr](https://kcuilla.github.io/reactablefmtr/) packages.

In order to build an interactive sparklines, dataui R package needs to be installed.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
remotes::install_github("timelyportfolio/dataui")
```
:::


Load the package onto R environment


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(dataui)
```
:::


### **Plotting interactive sparklines**

Prepare the list field


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
report <- report %>%
  group_by(Product) %>%
  summarize(`Monthly Sales` = list(Sales))
```
:::


Next, [react_sparkline](https://kcuilla.github.io/reactablefmtr/reference/react_sparkline.html) will be used to plot the sparklines

::: panel-tabset
